      • commoditySaveHandler

        private static javafx.event.EventHandler<javafx.event.ActionEvent> commoditySaveHandler
        Create a new commodity. Get the name of the commodity, its origin and its function from the commodityDialogueBox. Validate that no other commodity has the same name. If productive, iterate adding stocks of it to all industries. If consumption, iterate adding stocks to all social classes. Create at least one industry that makes this commodity and report on this fact.

      • makeAllTables

        public static void makeAllTables()
        Remake the tables. This has to be done whenever the stock columns change, because the commodities they represent have new names. There may be a better way but this is the simplest and I don't think it's expensive because there are no database operations involved.

      • refresh

        public static void refresh()
        Refresh the tables by requesting a reload of their data. This is called when there is a change to an item of data within a table (for example as a result of an edit) but the structure of the table has not changed. TODO check empirically if this is really needed because these are observables so in principle refresh should be automatic
